<br>
This is Arize again, I've posted on a few different lvl sections on places to get amazing exp.  For the 40's I strongly suggest Dreadlands outside Karnors Castle.  There are a few reasons why this tops exp in any other solo spot I've seen...<br>
<br>
1.  You can easily find clarities and sow's at your whim.  I haven't done more than probably 10 minutes of hunting with out a clarity at a time there.  There are ALWAYS enchanters either at Nwall or at the zoneline to Karnors.  Now that im high enough I often find clarity 2 which make the hunting even faster.  Usually I offer a Mod Rod, or if I happen to have a salis writ page or somethin as payment.  I tend not to ask the same enchanter twice as to not sound like im begging.  Usually there are three or four I can switch off between in order to make it look like the clarities are long and in between <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Sow's are no prob...there is always a different druid or shaman or ranger around to hook ya up.<br>
<br>
2.  Rez's are easy to get.  50+ clerics seem as easily found as sower's are.  Just drag your corpse to KC zoneline and look and there should be a 49 or 56 rez easily obtained.  i usually delve out 50pp or whatever I have on my body as payment.  I haven't gone without a 49+ rez since I've been there.<br>
<br>
As for the process that I use to hunt there goes as follows...<br>
<br>
Get a pet up and sit it down in an area that there aren't people around as to avoid mixing up pulls.  I generally go to NE corner but the whole east wall is usually pretty lowly populated.  Once you get sowed and clar'ed run out toward the east and grab something.  The mobs that are able to be killed relativly safely are Drachnid Silk(somethin) and Drachid Webmasters.  Drolvag Gnashers, and Stonegazer Cockatrice's.  The other versions of each of these should not be attempted until you hit 44 spells and even then only try Drachnid Widows, Petrafier Cockatrices and the occasional Drolvag Rager.  Varocious Brutes aren't too tough either.<br>
<br>
When it comes to bombing watch out for over bombin because the mobs WILL turn on you and you have to run em in circles until your pet can get them back on it.  You will probably have to through in the occasion pet heal when doing Drolvags because they tend to hit harder (at least imo).  Now that im 44 i like to use Elemental Maelstrom when startin the mob off.  250dd doesn't aggro the things as much as 585 at once and it does the same damage for compareable mana.  I then will smack em with a Blaze just to make sure I get over half their hp off on my own to get the full exp, and it also saves my pet some HP.  The amount of of DD's you have to use depends on the mob.  Drolvags take a Maelstrom and a SoS.  Then a finish off blaze.<br>
<br>
Prior to 45 I was getting a lvl of exp a day and it felt great when I realized that that was still possible at this lvl range.  Even at 45 I can still get nice exp...I will get through the lvl in 3 days which is nice as opposed to the two weeks it took me grouping in 40.  <br>
<br>
Anyway I hope this helps...Good Luck<br>
<br>
Arize<br>
